Locations.Name: Eeltown
Locations.Description: You find yourself in the middle of the bustling streets of EEL CITY. The few yellow window lights of the late afternoon twilight reflect softly on the street cobblestones.

Objects.Name: Eel
Objects.LookDescription: It's an eel just lying on the road!
Objects.SecondaryDialogue: You want me to join you? Sure I guess? Just grab me.

Dialogue topics.Subject: EELS
Dialogue topics.Response: There are many eels out there. I am but an eely drop in an eely ocean.
Dialogue topics.SecondaryResponse: Eels are eels. I've told you all I know.

Objects.Name: Tavern
Objects.LookDescription: You see a tavern just lying on the road!
Objects.GetDescription: You don't have enough money for this particular real estate.
Objects.MainDialogue: You try talking to a guy hanging out outside. He just tells you to leave him alone. Surprisingly rude. And not because I didn't want to write dialogue for him.

Objects.Name: Street
Objects.LookDescription: One of the streets slithering through EEL CITY. You see a sewer plate in the middle, and something that looks suspiciously like an eel on the ground.
Objects.MainDialogue: You try talking to all the people in the street at the same time and fail.

Locations.Name: Tavern
Locations.Description: The EEL TAIL is currently not very full. From what you can see, this place isn't fully implemented yet, which detracts a lot of customers from visiting. You see a BARTENDER and an exit leading back out.

Objects.Name: Bartender
Objects.LookDescription: Borktender. It's a dog. For some reason that's definitely not me wanting to make a pun.
Objects.GetDescription: You get the bartender and put him in your bag. Unfortunately, he exscapes.
Objects.MainDialogue: 'GIVE ME A DRINK, BORKTENDER.', you say. Unfortunately it's impossible to catch it in time.

Locations.Name: SEWERS
Locations.Description: Sewer count +1. There must be swarms of eels in the SEWAGE but no way to get them out. There's also a STICK on the ground.

Objects.Name: SEWAGE
Objects.GetDescription: You cup your hands and try to get some water, but fail.
Objects.MainDialogue: You ask the sewage how to get eels. The sewage faintly replies 'ITLL BE YEARS BEFORE YOU CAN CATCH US'.

Objects.Name: STICK
Objects.LookDescription: It's a debug stick. You can stick it up yours pal.
Objects.GetDescription: You get the stick despite its numerous protests.
Objects.MainDialogue: It says: 'dont pick me up bro.'
Objects.SecondaryDialogue: It says: 'no but for real dont do it pal'.
